==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*συνάγω / sunagō / soon-ag'-o

===Etymology===
*From [[σύν]] and [[ἄγω]]; to lead together, that is, collect or convene; specifically to entertain (hospitably): 

===Verb===
'''συνάγω'''

# [[accompany]], [[assemble]] (selves, together), bestow, come together, [[gather]] (selves together, up, together), lead into, resort, take in.

